definitions.title: Last Observation Carried Forward (LOCF)
definitions.problem: Missing values in longitudinal data need to be filled with the last known value.
definitions.whenToUse: When the analysis plan specifies LOCF for missing data handling in safety datasets.

definitions.title: Calculate BMI from Height and Weight
definitions.problem: Need to derive Body Mass Index (BMI) from raw height and weight variables.

implementations.rCode:
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

df_locf <- df %>%
  group_by(usubjid) %>%
  fill(aval, .direction = "down")
considerations: Ensure data is sorted by subject and time before applying.
Do not use for baseline imputation if baseline is missing.

implementations.sasCode:
if not missing(weight) and not missing(height) then 
  bmi = weight / ((height/100)**2);
considerations: Check units! Height is usually cm, weight kg.
